# .cursorrules — Read This First, Every Time

You are building **BetArena**, a full feature-for-feature clone of **Bet365 (bet365.com)** — the world's largest online sports betting platform. The only difference is that BetArena uses **virtual/demo credits** instead of real money. Everything else — the UI, the sports coverage, the bet types, the odds markets, the live betting experience, the navigation structure — must replicate Bet365 as closely as possible while having its own branding and slight creative touches.

---

## Your North Star: Bet365.com

Before building ANY feature, mentally ask yourself:
> "How does Bet365 do this?"

Then build it that way. If you are unsure how Bet365 handles something, default to the most feature-complete, professional implementation possible.

Study these Bet365 sections and replicate them:
- bet365.com → Sports lobby (left sidebar sport list, top navigation, in-play section)
- bet365.com → Any football match page (market accordion layout, odds buttons, bet slip)
- bet365.com → In-Play page (live match list, live score, live odds updating in real time)
- bet365.com → My Account → My Bets (open bets, settled bets, cash out button)
- bet365.com → Bet slip (right sidebar, add/remove selections, stake input, potential returns)

